#1 Resected stage II colon adenocarcinoma (T3, N0, M0)
Basic cancer education has been provided to the patient at the request of Dr. Davis service.  I have had the opportunity to review the operative report, surgical pathology, laboratory values, and notes in Documents Browser.  I have reviewed these findings with the patient and answered questions.  I have discussed this case in detail with Dr. Rivera, my collaborating physician, who has guided my plan.
We have discussed the characteristics of the cancer, including the type of malignancy, size, grade, lymph node status, and stage of the cancer.
We would like Mr. Locher to return in the outpatient setting for further evaluation and treatment recommendations.  To this end, I have ordered a CT-scan of the abdomen and pelvis (without contrast), chest x-ray, comprehensive lab panel including a CEA, MSI testing, and an appointment with us in Medical Oncology as well as a postoperative evaluation with Dr. Roberts.  He verbalized understanding and wishes to proceed.
PATIENT EDUCATION
Ready to learn, no apparent learning barriers were identified; learning preferences include listening.  Explained diagnosis and treatment plan; patient expressed understanding of the content.

[end section id="20112"]

